FBIS4-33693 "drlat112_b_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-112 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Minister Hails `Firm' OAS Message on Embargo Minister Hails `Firm' OAS Message on Embargo FL0906184494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 9 Jun 94 FL0906184494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] Claudette Werleigh, the Aristide government's foreign minister, considers the latest OAS General Assembly measure a very firm message to the de facto authorities in Haiti. The 34 OAS foreign ministers adopted a resolution on an embargo on commercial flights to and from Haiti and on freezing the financial assets of members of the Haitian provisional government: [Begin Werleigh recording, in Creole] This is why they mention in the resolution....[pauses] One of the last points involves working toward professionalizing the Army so that we can have an Army that protects the territory and helps us form the new police force provided for in our Constitution rather than one that tortures people, kills, and destroys. [end recording]
